During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders reiterated President Trump's statement expressing support for Senator John McCain, who was recently diagnosed with brain cancer. Sanders also discussed the Office of Management and Budget's release of the first update to the Trump administration's unified agenda for regulatory reform. Director of the Office of Management and Budget, Mick Mulvaney, spoke about the administration's goals for regulatory reform and the progress they have made in removing unnecessary regulations. Sanders also fielded questions about the President's confidence in Attorney General Jeff Sessions, the ongoing investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 election, and the administration's strategy in Afghanistan.